relevant_findings.general: Alert, oriented to name, place and situation. Fatigued appearing but comfortable, no acute signs of distress.
relevant_findings.head_neck: NCAT, Pupils equal and reactive, sclerae non-icteric, oropharynx clear, moist mucous membranes. Supple neck, no jugular venous distension, no thyromegaly. No cervical, supraclavicular or axillary lymphadenopathy.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: S1S2, regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, rubs or gallops.
relevant_findings.respiratory: Good air movement bilaterally, no rhonchi or wheezing.
relevant_findings.abdominal: Soft, non-tender, non-distended, positive bowel sounds.
relevant_findings.extremities: No lower leg edema, no clubbing or cyanosis.

physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initial vital signs showed a slightly lower heart rate and blood pressure with improved oxygen saturation after transfer.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Patient reports improved nausea with no abdominal pain.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Nausea improved over time from initial presentation.
